      "solution": "chomp($n=<>);\n$_=<>;\nif((length)%$n) {\n    print \"ERROR\\n\";\n} else {\n    s/(\\d{$n})/$s=0;map{$s^=$_}split('',$1);$s/ge;\n    print;\n}\n",
      "statement": "Given a bit string consisting of bits from a random bit source with an unknown skew, the skew can be reduced as follows: Take the bits in non-overlapping groups of [[n]] bits from left to right and replace them by the parity of each group.\n\nThe parity of a group of bits is the least-significant bit of their sum, or equivalently, all bits XORed together. For example, the parity of 0101 is 0.\n\nYour objective: Deskew the bit string!\n\nIf the number of input bits is not a multiple of [[n]], output {{ERROR}}. Otherwise output the resulting deskewed bit string.",
