    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Given a bit string consisting of bits from a random bit source with an unknown skew, the skew can be reduced as follows: Take the bits in non-overlapping groups of <var>n</var> bits from left to right and replace them by the parity of each group.<br><br>The parity of a group of bits is the least-significant bit of their sum, or equivalently, all bits XORed together. For example, the parity of 0101 is 0.<br><br>Your objective: Deskew the bit string!<br><br>If the number of input bits is not a multiple of <var>n</var>, output <const>ERROR</const>. Otherwise output the resulting deskewed bit string.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> The number of bits <var>n</var> for each group.<br><strong>Line 2:</strong> A binary string <var>str</var>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> The deskewed bit string or the string <const>ERROR</const>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &lt;= <var>n</var> &lt;= 64 <br><var>str</var> consists of zeros and ones (1 &lt;= length &lt;= 1000)</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">2\n10111011</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      